  "text": "In a Bayesian setting, before any data is considered, f is treated as a Gaussian Process, i.e., it is assumed that for any finite set of configurations {\u03c1 i, i = 1, . . . N } the values f (\u03c1 i ) taken by the vector function f are well described by a multivariate Gaussian distribution [CITATION_1] . We write:",
